            <title>[THRIFT-866] term() in spec definitions seems to not work in erlang R12</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-866</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For full description see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-599&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t use unnecessary processes in the Erlang transports and clients&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-599&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-599&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but the gist seems to be that the use of term() in spec definitions doesn&apos;t compile for  R12B3 on debian.  Since R12 works and since any() is supposed to be a synonym, it would probably be a good idea to change all instances of term to any for now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
